Level 212, colloquially known as "Saturday Morning", or "The Living Cartoon", is the 213<sup>th</sup> documented level of [[Backrooms Wiki|
'''The Backrooms,''']] and is one of the few levels accessible from baseline reality.

== <span style="color: #fccf03; text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px, #020d6e 0px 6px 0px; font-family:SF Minced Meat;"><big>Description</big></span> ==
{{Blurimage|caption=<span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 2px 0px;">A photo of Level 212.</span>|file=212firstphoto.png}}
{{Blurimage|caption=<span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px;">Another photo of Level 212, taken in a minamalistic area.</span>|file=212secondphoto.png}}
Level 212 appears as an infinite suburban household with similar architecture to American children's animation programs of the near-late 20th century. The house's construction fluctuates rapidly based on perspective, which means that at one angle, the ceiling may appear very far off the ground, but from another is relatively close. The levels cartoon nature and physics-bending proportions make it appear 2-dimensional, compared to reality.

No one room within the house is the same in construction nor appearance style, and height varies greatly from one room to the next. Each room follows a unique design, ranging from fully shaded rooms with accurate depiction of the physics of light, similar to shows like ''Spongebob'', to minimalist rooms with little to no shadow, resembling that of ''Ren & Stimpy,'' or the original 1950's version of ''Rocky and Bullwinkle''.

Most of the rooms within Level 212 is fully furnished, and decorated with wall art, aesthetic appliances like chandeliers and light bulbs, and old box TVs. All furniture within the household is larger than it's [[The Frontrooms|'''Frontrooms''']] equivalent, but for the most part serves the same purpose. The bath and kitchen appliances fully function as well as the TVs, though said TVs just display nonsense programming, like illegible news broadcasts or public television.

Level 212's corridors mainly twist and bend in odd ways, most times defying the laws of physics, like doors leading to each other, entering a door and heading to one room, then re-entering the same door later, leading to a different area, and strange gravitational anomalies, like walking upside-down perfectly fine, as well as light fixtures 
hanging upwards. Some rooms in the level also are upside down, with furniture resting on the ceiling instead of the floor. Several windows are located on the level, displaying other levels on the other side, which can be entered by breaking the window.

The cleanliness of the rooms varies as well, as some rooms may be in pristine condition, with exaggerated shines gleaming on every item within, and some may be absolutely filthy, with rotting walls, green sludge everywhere, and cartoonishly oversized mice. For the most part, the rooms within the household seem to alternate between these two states.

The layout of Level 212 is as random as the architecture, as random rooms could link to one another, like a bedroom leading to a kitchen, and a garage leading to a bathroom. The level's random layout and exaggerated nature means that attempting to draw a map of any kind is infeasible.

The level's atmosphere consists of playful orchestral music consisting mainly of brass, similar to the likes of ''Looney Toons''. The music seems to adjust fluidly to correspond to the situation a wanderer finds themselves in, for example, if the wanderer is being chased, the music will play loud and fast, and vice versa. The music is able to be heard from both ears, and is even picked up by recording instruments.  
==<span style="color: #fccf03; text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px, #020d6e 0px 6px 0px; font-family:SF Minced Meat;"><big>Entities</big></span>==

=== <span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px; font-family:Bagel Fat One">Loonies</span> ===
{{Blurimage|caption=<span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px;">A photo of a Looney taken from behind.</span>|file=212photooflooney.png}}
The main (and possibly only) threat residing in Level 212 is their respective entity, commonly known as Loonies (sing. "Looney"). Loonies are small humanoid beings with exaggerated proportions and anatomy, usually ranging under 5 feet tall, and act in almost a cartoonish manner. These beings appear to have varying intelligence, with some barely being able to solve simple problems, and others being able to navigate tight and winding corridors. The only common property all these Loonies posses is a severe hostility to all living beings. Loonies all have clothe-like appendages, typically around the waist area, usually resemblent of pale white undergarments.
== <span style="color: #fccf03; text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px, #020d6e 0px 6px 0px; font-family:SF Minced Meat;"><big>Colonies & Outposts</big></span> ==
Due to the level's abnormal layout and danger, establishing any colonies or outposts are infeasible.

== <span style="color: #fccf03; text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px, #020d6e 0px 6px 0px; font-family:SF Minced Meat;"><big>Entrances & Exits</big></span> ==
=== <span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px; font-family:Bagel Fat One">Entrances</span> ===

* No-clipping through a television displaying classic cartoons from the 1950-2000 time period could lead you here.
* Entering a random animation area within [[Level 501|'''Level 501''']] and passing out will lead you here.
* Remembering an old television show in [[Level 18|'''Level 18''']] and noclipping through where it's playing has a rare chance to lead one here.
=== <span style="text-shadow: #02083d 0px 3px 0px; font-family:Bagel Fat One">Exits</span> ===

* Breaking a window will take you a random level, specifically the one displayed on the other side.
* Noclipping through a broken piece of furniture will take one to [[Level 9|'''Level 9''']].
* Re-noclipping through a TV could be a [[Level 398|'''way back''']].
* Consuming the corpses of a deceased Looney will take one to [[Level 502|'''Level 502''']].
* Climbing a specific set of stairs leading to a white void will take one to [[Level 460|'''Level 460''']].
* Eating the food within the fridges and passing out will take one to [[Level 33|'''Level 33''']].
* Falling down a dark pit will take one to [[Level 6|'''Level 6''']].
